The HASKELL INSTITUTE STUDENTS ACTIVITIES ASSOCIATION, a Corporation, v. Agnes Quapaw HOFFMAN et al. No. 1324. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 9, 1935. Gorrill & Asher, of Lawrence, Kan., for appellant. Thompson & Roberts, of Joplin, Mo., for appellees.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, for failure to prosecute.
